This paper discusses the challenges and approaches to building AI systems that are ethically bounded, which falls under the category of AI. The paper also mentions the need for flexibility and adaptability in AI, which is a common topic in robotics (RO). The ethical challenges of AI deployment also relate to cybersecurity (CY) and the need for secure and trustworthy systems. The paper also mentions the use of modular and compositional approaches, which are common in software engineering (SE). Finally, the paper touches on the need for ethical principles and guidelines, which could fall under the category of cryptography (CR) as it relates to secure communication and information sharing.
